cs.LO, cs.DM, cs.FL, cs.PL, cs.TC 

The paper deals with the formalism of membrane systems, which is a topic in theoretical computer science. The paper discusses the dependencies and simultaneity in membrane system computations, which are concepts related to logic and discrete mathematics. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of zero-safe nets, which are a type of Petri nets, and event structures, which are a topic in formal language theory. Hence, cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) and cs.PL (Programming Languages) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the synchronization of transitions, which is a topic in theoretical computer science and distributed computing, making cs.TC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
